Daud Olatunji, Abeokuta A former majority leader of the Ogun House of Assembly, Mr Yinka  Mafe, is dead. The former leader reportedly  died on Tuesday, same day he marked his 46th birthday. Mafe, a member of the seventh and eighth assemblies in the state, was said to have complained of chest pains on Tuesday after the birthday party  and died shortly after. The Speaker of the Ogun State House of Assembly, Olakunle  Oluomo, described the death of  Mafe as shocking and painful. The speaker in a statement by his media aide, Bukola Adeyinka, on Wednesday, said, “The state has lost a rare gem and a politician per excellence.” Also, the All Progressives Congress in Ogun in a statement by the  Publicity Secretary of its caretaker committee, Tunde Oladunjoye,  said,  “Indeed the people of Sagamu 1 constituency, the APC prays that God will give the family the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss.” Meanwhile, the governorship candidate of the Allied People’s Movement, Adekunle  Akinlade, in a statement by his media aide, said, “Words failed me in expressing the shock I felt when the news was  broken  that Asiwaju Yinka Mafe was dead. He was our friend, our brother and a very loyal ally in our political sojourn.” Copyright PUNCH.
